{{Infobox brand | logo = Optiarc.svg | logo_upright = 0.75 | name = Optiarc | currentowner = [[Vinpower]] | previousowners = [[Sony]], [[NEC]] | country = US | introduced = April 3, 2006 | discountinued = no | producttype = [[Consumer electronics]] | website = {{url|www.optiarcinc.com}} }}
'''Optiarc''' is a brand of optical desk drives owned by a US company [[Vinpower]], Inc.
Initially Optiarc was established on April 3, 2006 as a [[joint venture]] between [[Sony corporation|Sony Corporation]] (55% shares) and [[NEC Corporation]] (45% shares). The company, named '''Sony NEC Optiarc''', focused on manufacturing optical disk drives primarily for the [[OEM]] desktop and [[notebook PC]] markets.
On September 11, 2008, it was announced that Sony would take over NEC's 45% share, making Optiarc a wholly owned subsidiary of Sony,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sonynec-optiarc.com/company/index.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2008-12-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081218151311/http://www.sonynec-optiarc.com/company/index.html |archive-date=2008-12-18 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> to be called '''Sony Optiarc'''. This took effect on December 5, 2008<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sonynec-optiarc.com/company/principles.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2008-12-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100124141957/http://www.sonynec-optiarc.com/company/principles.html |archive-date=2010-01-24 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>
In March 2013, Sony closed its Optiarc optical disk division,<ref>{{cite news|last=Crothers|first=Brooke|title=Sony to exit PC-use optical drives, say reports|url=http://news.cnet.com/8301-1001_3-57501393-92/sony-to-exit-pc-use-optical-drives-say-reports/|accessdate=22 May 2014|newspaper=[[CNET]]|date=27 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Carter|first=White|title=Sony Optiarc closed, the subsidiary that manufactures optical drives|url=http://technewspedia.com/sony-optiarc-closed-the-subsidiary-that-manufactures-optical-drives/|accessdate=22 May 2014|newspaper=Technewspedia|date=27 August 2012}}</ref> laying off about 400 employees globally.
In 2017, a US company [[Vinpower]], whose main business was manufacturing optical disc duplicators for the commercial market, acquired rights to the Optiarc brand and product line.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.myce.com/news/u-s-company-vinpower-digital-claims-resurrecting-optiarc-cddvd-burner-brand-82160/|title=U.S. company VinPower Digital claims to be resurrecting Optiarc CD/DVD burner brand|last=Jan Willem|first=Aldershoff|date=June 19, 2017|work=Myce.com|access-date=April 26, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>
[[File:Sony Optiarc AD-7240S.jpg|thumb|left|Sony Optiarc DVD drive AD-7240S.]] {{clear|left}}
