In [[Devon]] and [[Cornwall]], '''tin coinage''' was a tax on [[white tin|refined tin]], payable to the [[Duchy of Cornwall]] and administered in the [[Stannary|Stannary Towns]].  The oldest surviving records of coinage show that it was collected in 1156.  It was abolished by the [[Tin Duties Act 1838]].

